{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":506,"text":"So, how many of you have ever"},{"time":1913,"text":"gotten behind the wheel of a car"},{"time":3568,"text":"when you really shouldn't have been driving?"},{"time":9255,"text":"Maybe you're out on the road for a long day,"},{"time":11160,"text":"and you just wanted to get home."},{"time":12650,"text":"You were tired, but you felt you could drive a few more miles."},{"time":15297,"text":"Maybe you thought,"},{"time":16496,"text":"I've had less to drink than everybody else,"},{"time":18513,"text":"I should be the one to go home."},{"time":20249,"text":"Or maybe your mind was just entirely elsewhere."}]},{"cues":[{"time":24840,"text":"Does this sound familiar to you?"},{"time":26294,"text":"Now, in those situations, wouldn't it be great"},{"time":29192,"text":"if there was a button on your dashboard"},{"time":30785,"text":"that you could push, and the car would get you home safely?"},{"time":37128,"text":"Now, that's been the promise of the self-driving car,"},{"time":39421,"text":"the autonomous vehicle, and it's been the dream"},{"time":42048,"text":"since at least 1939, when General Motors showcased"},{"time":45297,"text":"this idea at their Futurama booth at the World's Fair."}]},{"cues":[{"time":48599,"text":"Now, it's been one of those dreams"},{"time":50542,"text":"that's always seemed about 20 years in the future."},{"time":54756,"text":"Now, two weeks ago, that dream took a step forward,"},{"time":57439,"text":"when the state of Nevada granted Google's self-driving car"},{"time":60704,"text":"the very first license for an autonomous vehicle,"},{"time":64304,"text":"clearly establishing that it's legal for them"},{"time":66549,"text":"to test it on the roads in Nevada."},{"time":68359,"text":"Now, California's considering similar legislation,"},{"time":72086,"text":"and this would make sure that the autonomous car"},{"time":74494,"text":"is not one of those things that has to stay in Vegas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":77471,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":79567,"text":"Now, in my lab at Stanford, we've been working on"},{"time":83351,"text":"autonomous cars too, but with a slightly different spin"},{"time":86838,"text":"on things. You see, we've been developing robotic race cars,"},{"time":91086,"text":"cars that can actually push themselves to the very limits"},{"time":95206,"text":"of physical performance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":97446,"text":"Now, why would we want to do such a thing?"},{"time":100059,"text":"Well, there's two really good reasons for this."},{"time":102159,"text":"First, we believe that before people turn over control"},{"time":106118,"text":"to an autonomous car, that autonomous car should be"},{"time":108952,"text":"at least as good as the very best human drivers."},{"time":112206,"text":"Now, if you're like me, and the other 70 percent of the population"},{"time":115511,"text":"who know that we are above-average drivers,"},{"time":117704,"text":"you understand that's a very high bar."},{"time":120879,"text":"There's another reason as well."},{"time":123271,"text":"Just like race car drivers can use all of the friction"},{"time":126847,"text":"between the tire and the road,"},{"time":128127,"text":"all of the car's capabilities to go as fast as possible,"},{"time":131304,"text":"we want to use all of those capabilities to avoid"},{"time":134649,"text":"any accident we can."}]},{"cues":[{"time":136237,"text":"Now, you may push the car to the limits"},{"time":138287,"text":"not because you're driving too fast,"},{"time":140254,"text":"but because you've hit an icy patch of road,"},{"time":142414,"text":"conditions have changed."},{"time":144118,"text":"In those situations, we want a car"},{"time":146879,"text":"that is capable enough to avoid any accident"},{"time":150599,"text":"that can physically be avoided."}]},{"cues":[{"time":153277,"text":"I must confess, there's kind of a third motivation as well."},{"time":157544,"text":"You see, I have a passion for racing."},{"time":159800,"text":"In the past, I've been a race car owner,"},{"time":162564,"text":"a crew chief and a driving coach,"},{"time":165119,"text":"although maybe not at the level that you're currently expecting."},{"time":168974,"text":"One of the things that we've developed in the lab --"},{"time":171678,"text":"we've developed several vehicles --"},{"time":173382,"text":"is what we believe is the world's first"},{"time":175617,"text":"autonomously drifting car."},{"time":177982,"text":"It's another one of those categories"},{"time":180495,"text":"where maybe there's not a lot of competition."}]},{"cues":[{"time":182918,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":184326,"text":"But this is P1. It's an entirely student-built electric vehicle,"},{"time":188148,"text":"which through using its rear-wheel drive"},{"time":190226,"text":"and front-wheel steer-by-wire"},{"time":191791,"text":"can drift around corners."},{"time":193858,"text":"It can get sideways like a rally car driver,"},{"time":196058,"text":"always able to take the tightest curve,"},{"time":197773,"text":"even on slippery, changing surfaces,"},{"time":201077,"text":"never spinning out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":202693,"text":"We've also worked with Volkswagen Oracle,"},{"time":205061,"text":"on Shelley, an autonomous race car that has raced"},{"time":208485,"text":"at 150 miles an hour through the Bonneville Salt Flats,"},{"time":211555,"text":"gone around Thunderhill Raceway Park in the sun,"},{"time":216026,"text":"the wind and the rain,"},{"time":218665,"text":"and navigated the 153 turns and 12.4 miles"},{"time":223683,"text":"of the Pikes Peak Hill Climb route"},{"time":225245,"text":"in Colorado with nobody at the wheel."}]},{"cues":[{"time":228718,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":230166,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":235732,"text":"I guess it goes without saying that we've had a lot of fun"},{"time":239011,"text":"doing this."},{"time":240315,"text":"But in fact, there's something else that we've developed"},{"time":243972,"text":"in the process of developing these autonomous cars."},{"time":247027,"text":"We have developed a tremendous appreciation"},{"time":250898,"text":"for the capabilities of human race car drivers."},{"time":254715,"text":"As we've looked at the question of how well do these cars perform,"},{"time":259060,"text":"we wanted to compare them to our human counterparts."},{"time":262339,"text":"And we discovered their human counterparts are amazing."},{"time":268019,"text":"Now, we can take a map of a race track,"},{"time":272042,"text":"we can take a mathematical model of a car,"},{"time":274412,"text":"and with some iteration, we can actually find"},{"time":277315,"text":"the fastest way around that track."},{"time":278940,"text":"We line that up with data that we record"},{"time":281473,"text":"from a professional driver,"},{"time":282906,"text":"and the resemblance is absolutely remarkable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":287013,"text":"Yes, there are subtle differences here,"},{"time":290225,"text":"but the human race car driver is able to go out"},{"time":293352,"text":"and drive an amazingly fast line,"},{"time":295687,"text":"without the benefit of an algorithm that compares"},{"time":298017,"text":"the trade-off between going as fast as possible"},{"time":300625,"text":"in this corner, and shaving a little bit of time"},{"time":302662,"text":"off of the straight over here."},{"time":304564,"text":"Not only that, they're able to do it lap"},{"time":308021,"text":"after lap after lap."},{"time":310396,"text":"They're able to go out and consistently do this,"},{"time":313308,"text":"pushing the car to the limits every single time."},{"time":317436,"text":"It's extraordinary to watch."},{"time":320605,"text":"You put them in a new car,"},{"time":322671,"text":"and after a few laps, they've found the fastest line in that car,"},{"time":326573,"text":"and they're off to the races."}]},{"cues":[{"time":330450,"text":"It really makes you think,"},{"time":331596,"text":"we'd love to know what's going on inside their brain."},{"time":336467,"text":"So as researchers, that's what we decided to find out."},{"time":341008,"text":"We decided to instrument not only the car,"},{"time":342820,"text":"but also the race car driver,"},{"time":345315,"text":"to try to get a glimpse into what was going on"},{"time":348084,"text":"in their head as they were doing this."},{"time":350270,"text":"Now, this is Dr. Lene Harbott applying electrodes"},{"time":354220,"text":"to the head of John Morton."},{"time":355452,"text":"John Morton is a former Can-Am and IMSA driver,"},{"time":358441,"text":"who's also a class champion at Le Mans."},{"time":360241,"text":"Fantastic driver, and very willing to put up with graduate students"},{"time":363737,"text":"and this sort of research."},{"time":365592,"text":"She's putting electrodes on his head"},{"time":368264,"text":"so that we can monitor the electrical activity"},{"time":370376,"text":"in John's brain as he races around the track."}]},{"cues":[{"time":373208,"text":"Now, clearly we're not going to put a couple of electrodes on his head"},{"time":376403,"text":"and understand exactly what all of his thoughts are on the track."},{"time":379673,"text":"However, neuroscientists have identified certain patterns"},{"time":383080,"text":"that let us tease out some very important aspects of this."},{"time":386841,"text":"For instance, the resting brain"},{"time":388688,"text":"tends to generate a lot of alpha waves."},{"time":390843,"text":"In contrast, theta waves are associated with"},{"time":394595,"text":"a lot of cognitive activity, like visual processing,"},{"time":397779,"text":"things where the driver is thinking quite a bit."},{"time":400827,"text":"Now, we can measure this,"},{"time":402490,"text":"and we can look at the relative power"},{"time":404475,"text":"between the theta waves and the alpha waves."},{"time":406675,"text":"This gives us a measure of mental workload,"},{"time":409117,"text":"how much the driver is actually challenged cognitively"},{"time":412684,"text":"at any point along the track."}]},{"cues":[{"time":414470,"text":"Now, we wanted to see if we could actually record this"},{"time":417412,"text":"on the track, so we headed down south to Laguna Seca."},{"time":420450,"text":"Laguna Seca is a legendary raceway"},{"time":422466,"text":"about halfway between Salinas and Monterey."},{"time":424767,"text":"It has a curve there called the Corkscrew."},{"time":426854,"text":"Now, the Corkscrew is a chicane, followed by a quick"},{"time":429571,"text":"right-handed turn as the road drops three stories."},{"time":432317,"text":"Now, the strategy for driving this as explained to me was,"},{"time":436083,"text":"you aim for the bush in the distance,"},{"time":438105,"text":"and as the road falls away, you realize it was actually the top of a tree."}]},{"cues":[{"time":441130,"text":"All right, so thanks to the Revs Program at Stanford,"},{"time":444434,"text":"we were able to take John there"},{"time":445907,"text":"and put him behind the wheel"},{"time":446871,"text":"of a 1960 Porsche Abarth Carrera."},{"time":449310,"text":"Life is way too short for boring cars."},{"time":453008,"text":"So, here you see John on the track,"},{"time":454767,"text":"he's going up the hill -- Oh! Somebody liked that --"},{"time":456951,"text":"and you can see, actually, his mental workload"},{"time":459416,"text":"-- measuring here in the red bar --"},{"time":461569,"text":"you can see his actions as he approaches."},{"time":463912,"text":"Now watch, he has to downshift."},{"time":467142,"text":"And then he has to turn left."},{"time":467903,"text":"Look for the tree, and down."}]},{"cues":[{"time":471896,"text":"Not surprisingly, you can see this is a pretty challenging task."},{"time":474734,"text":"You can see his mental workload spike as he goes through this,"},{"time":477710,"text":"as you would expect with something that requires"},{"time":479774,"text":"this level of complexity."},{"time":482583,"text":"But what's really interesting is to look at areas of the track"},{"time":485999,"text":"where his mental workload doesn't increase."},{"time":488845,"text":"I'm going to take you around now"},{"time":490340,"text":"to the other side of the track."},{"time":491429,"text":"Turn three. And John's going to go into that corner"},{"time":493765,"text":"and the rear end of the car is going to begin to slide out."},{"time":496316,"text":"He's going to have to correct for that with steering."},{"time":498333,"text":"So watch as John does this here."},{"time":500564,"text":"Watch the mental workload, and watch the steering."},{"time":502886,"text":"The car begins to slide out, dramatic maneuver to correct it,"},{"time":506558,"text":"and no change whatsoever in the mental workload."},{"time":510081,"text":"Not a challenging task."},{"time":512913,"text":"In fact, entirely reflexive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":516113,"text":"Now, our data processing on this is still preliminary,"},{"time":519756,"text":"but it really seems that these phenomenal feats"},{"time":522428,"text":"that the race car drivers are performing"},{"time":524038,"text":"are instinctive."},{"time":525948,"text":"They are things that they have simply learned to do."},{"time":529338,"text":"It requires very little mental workload"},{"time":531620,"text":"for them to perform these amazing feats."},{"time":534444,"text":"And their actions are fantastic."},{"time":537579,"text":"This is exactly what you want to do on the steering wheel"},{"time":540190,"text":"to catch the car in this situation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":543527,"text":"Now, this has given us tremendous insight"},{"time":546972,"text":"and inspiration for our own autonomous vehicles."},{"time":550094,"text":"We've started to ask the question:"},{"time":552022,"text":"Can we make them a little less algorithmic"},{"time":554275,"text":"and a little more intuitive?"},{"time":556724,"text":"Can we take this reflexive action"},{"time":559005,"text":"that we see from the very best race car drivers,"},{"time":561292,"text":"introduce it to our cars,"},{"time":562941,"text":"and maybe even into a system that could"},{"time":564925,"text":"get onto your car in the future?"},{"time":566893,"text":"That would take us a long step"},{"time":568504,"text":"along the road to autonomous vehicles"},{"time":571013,"text":"that drive as well as the best humans."}]},{"cues":[{"time":572925,"text":"But it's made us think a little bit more deeply as well."},{"time":576365,"text":"Do we want something more from our car"},{"time":579333,"text":"than to simply be a chauffeur?"},{"time":581173,"text":"Do we want our car to perhaps be a partner, a coach,"},{"time":585408,"text":"someone that can use their understanding of the situation"},{"time":588495,"text":"to help us reach our potential?"},{"time":592751,"text":"Can, in fact, the technology not simply replace humans,"},{"time":595024,"text":"but allow us to reach the level of reflex and intuition"},{"time":599599,"text":"that we're all capable of?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":603024,"text":"So, as we move forward into this technological future,"},{"time":604947,"text":"I want you to just pause and think of that for a moment."},{"time":607768,"text":"What is the ideal balance of human and machine?"},{"time":611543,"text":"And as we think about that,"},{"time":613252,"text":"let's take inspiration"},{"time":614983,"text":"from the absolutely amazing capabilities"},{"time":618312,"text":"of the human body and the human mind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":621128,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":622864,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}